snippet: PATH car No. 745 is the astonishingly intact remnant of a seven-car train that was waiting on Track 2 at the World Trade Center terminal on Sept. 11, 2001.
abstract: PATH train car No 745, vintage 1970s model that was among two surviving cars that were stationed under World Trade Center on Sept 11, 2001, arrives in East Haven, Conn, where it will reside in Shore Line Trolley Museum; car is scheduled to be installed in museum in 2016.
lead_paragraph: PATH car No. 745 is the astonishingly intact remnant of a seven-car train that was waiting on Track 2 at the World Trade Center terminal on Sept. 11, 2001.

headline.main: A 9/11 Artifact Heads to Its New Home at Connecticut’s Shore Line Trolley Museum
